Cross-reference:  For construction of a revised statute, see s. 990.001 (7) and
cases cited under s. 990.001.
Reports or comments of nonlegislative committees incorporated in the Legisla-
tive Reference Bureau analysis under sub. (1) (b) 2. are valid aids in interpreting a
statute that originated from the committee.  Thompson v. Allaert, 80 Wis. 2d 285,
259 N.W.2d 54 (1977).
The duties under s. 13.93 (2) [now sub. (2) (j) to (L)] are mainly ministerial and
editorial;  the  revisor  [now  the  Legislative  Reference  Bureau]  rarely  proposes  any
substantive changes in the law, and, if it does, the changes are very minor.
